column1: #Text=Reed 1550 4750 Nov. 20 The Morning Light is one of the fastest and most magnificent clippers in the world.
#Text=She is sister ship to the celebrated clipper White Star, and has made the astonishing passages of 71 and 73 days from Liverpool to Melbourne.
#Text=Her saloon accommodations are of the roost extensive character, splendidly famished, and replete with every appurtenance for the comfortable enjoyment of the voyage.
#Text=In a vessel of her majestic size the apartments for second cabin, intermediate, and steerage passengers are lofty, reomy, and well ventilated.
#Text=Captain Gillies has earned a high reputation in the Australian trade during his many passages in this noble clipper.
#Text=Suitable passengers by the Morning Light may obtain land grants for 40 acres of land in New Zealand from the Provincial Agents, for a list of whom, and all information, apply to H.
#Text=WILSON and CHAMBERS, 21, Water-street, Liverpool; or to
#Text=ON SALE, a Four-iift BEER ENGINE, in good condition.
